<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<head>
  <meta charset="UTF-8">
  <title>Subscription Cancelled - Admin Notification</title>
  <style>
    body {
      font-family: Arial, sans-serif;
      font-size: 14px;
      color: #333;
    }

    .container {
      max-width: 600px;
      margin: auto;
      padding: 20px;
      border: 1px solid #eee;
    }

    .logo {
      text-align: center;
      margin-bottom: 20px;
    }

    .logo img {
      max-height: 60px;
    }

    .header {
      text-align: center;
      font-size: 20px;
      margin-bottom: 20px;
      color: #e67e22;
    }

    .content p {
      margin-bottom: 15px;
    }

    .details {
      border-top: 1px solid #ccc;
      padding-top: 10px;
      margin-top: 20px;
    }

    .details strong {
      display: inline-block;
      width: 140px;
    }

    .footer {
      font-size: 12px;
      color: #777;
      text-align: center;
      margin-top: 30px;
    }
  </style>
</head>
<body>
  <div class="container">
    <div class="logo">
      <img src="{{ logoUrl }}" alt="Logo">
    </div>

    <div class="header">
      Subscription Cancelled After Failed Payments
    </div>

    <div class="content">
      <p>A customer's subscription has been <strong>cancelled</strong> after three failed payment attempts.</p>

      <div class="details">
        <p><strong>Customer Name:</strong> {{firstName}} {{lastName}}</p>
        <p><strong>Email:</strong> {{email}}</p>
        <p><strong>Subscription ID:</strong> {{subscriptionId}}</p>
        <p><strong>Reason:</strong> Payment failed 3 times</p>
      </div>

      <p>Please take any follow-up action if required.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="footer">
      This is an automated message from your store notification system.
    </div>
  </div>
</body>
</html>